Bai Qingyang

The epidemic is worrying, and the day-to-day negative news is exhausting.

In the vast sea of information, it is difficult to distinguish the true from the false, kindness and patience disappear together.

The world, the nation and the heart in the struggle for the right to speak, a knife after a knife, cut deeper than WHO. And the wound is not in each other, it's in us.

In this moment, we place our hopes in literature.

Teacher Yan Paints the details, and he also paints the day we spend.

Heaven and earth are not kind, take all things as the straw dog. All are experiencing the same suffering, and all are experiencing the same joy. As long as there is a fire in the dark night, we will be warm.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Even though most of it is dark, there is this dazzling light.

January twenty-three,

Wuhan has banned the city from the land. It is not impossible to isolate a city; the order is the invisible wall; and man is the physical load that joins the wall together.

Only eight days. It's all over the news. The most common words are "progress" , "hope" and "need to know" . The rumor breaks through the rumor, the reason induction reason. The era of divergent views, in addition to calculating the distance between two meters between people are not infected, there are people, how far away, how close. Make the person that alienates has warmth, the person that is close is not strange.

The doctor was on call day and night. Wuhan has been transformed from a circulating center into an isolated island. It is the hope of the people, but it is the dust of the face that is bigger. Hope is always rare; because it is rare, it is always compared to fire. The firelight, even a little bit, is dazzling, but one always forgets that the greater darkness surrounds the firelight.

In Wuhan, people who don't go to the hospital are afraid of people who go there. Inside China, people in out-of-town provinces fear Hubei People. Between countries, people who are not Chinese are afraid of the Chinese. When human nature and human nature have a collision, shouting slogans, called moral; personal expression, is human nature. The one who can restrain human nature and keep his integrity is called divine nature.

Those who possess divinity are always in the minority; those who possess humanity, however, are born with it and are never given up.

Panic spreads panic, suddenly the world was part of the uneasy, slowly infected into everyone all the time trembling. Masks in Hong Kong have been out of stock since late December. Yesterday announced a "limited purchase of a box" , so that the day is not bright, people have long lines. My aunt came back from the market and told me: There are rare people in the market today, but few stallholders.

I always thought that the world is rational, but the world is never as fact, the world is more like a dream. It's not what you expect, it's what you do. It's what happens.

That's what I learned. I panicked.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Take each other's hands.

January twenty-four,

I can't go out there alone, going from the news to the edge. Witnessed the closure of the city of Wuhan, the Spring Festival in each individual's ordinary habits, witnessed one after another plausible truth. Everyone wants the truth, but everyone ignores it. The truth isn't clear. And you never will.

January twenty-five,

I began to pass the time, but the restlessness and anxiety had reached a boiling point. I don't go out. I don't socialize. Shut yourself in your room and greet all your friends in Wuhan. They're like me. We know as much as you do, and no one knows more than you do.

January twenty-six,

Some Hubei people returned home and were isolated by the villagers. After a forty-eight, hour journey, the homeless people of Wuhan walked back along the blocked Yangtze River Bridge. I can't remember the details of the story, but the point is, there are people who don't have an easy life. I booked my flight to London today. Just popped in to pay a visit to a friend. It's not so much visiting as sitting down, sitting down, just waiting to die.

January twenty-seven,

There is no weather, the mood is a lot of ease. As the day to leave more and more close to the home, more and more deep, one second want to escape, in the escape to become a fact, and have a family. That's why I say, "closeness is only in the distance. ". That night, I wrote, "I said that not caring about the world may be selfish. "

January twenty-eight,

As feelings of insecurity move from turbulent to turbulent, people become accustomed to change. I had this conversation with a friend, and I said, "aren't you afraid of the news? "? "Not Afraid. Sooner or later, we're GONNA have a disease like this, and I don't like it when it's all over the news. Tell me one thing. I mean, there are more important things than this, but why don't people talk about it, just because it affects people of all classes, but soon I understood why his composure seemed overwhelming.

The phenomenon is always local, but the problem of vigilance is comprehensive. The number of deaths can not be masked, but the increase in numbers can be mixed. By January twenty-eight, the death rate was estimated to be less than 4 percent. If the actual number of people infected, the mortality rate may be less than 0.01% . At that stage of the speculation, there wasn't a huge difference in mortality rates between coronaviruses and influenza.

Of course, that's just me agreeing with him. But what is often overlooked is that the flu kills close to five hundred thousand people a year.

When disaster becomes commonplace, or stable, the term is removed and replaced by science that can explain it. People are not afraid of anything that can be explained, and they are always hopeful about science. Just as people can be understood by giving the right reasons for evil human nature. Once understood, there is half as much to be blamed for.

January twenty-nine,

It's still panic. There's been a cease-and-desist, a cease-and-desist. But I had no connection to the world. It was only when I announced the end that I realized something was missing.

January 30,

My aunt and I complained that there was not much left in the market, not even enough spices to buy. It was also mentioned that people from China are running to Thailand now, and the Thai government is not stopping them. On the Internet, some abuse, some understand, abuse less than half. The discussion was cut in half. No one said one more thing. But soon, Vulcan Mountain Hospital was built in a matter of days. They're all alive. Why Alive?

January thirty-one,

Today. The World Health Organization has declared a state of emergency for global health, but not for trade or individual travel. Some people like it. Well, it's a little better than I expected. People are busy trying to bury the hatchet, and organizations are busy trying to work together. They say it's a battle we must win. I still didn't go out. Even for the next two days of travel, is not prepared, but added peace of mind.

I can't tell you what to look at objectively and what to do. But that's the way society is, and that's how everyone is part of it. The job that is handed out to you may simply be to not influence the other members to do it.

Human Nature is the night, even if only a little bit of fire, but it is the only place we can see. With the light, everything in the night is ignored. We only focus on the foot, lit by the light of each step.
